I highly suggest that you do all our research before buying a policy from New York Life. Their administrator (Henchmen) UNUM is know for turning down policies. Just Google it and look at the expose done by 60 Minutes years ago. Based on my experience, things haven't changed. Policy holder for over 25 years, on disability since October and still dealing with them. They want additional information to support THEIR doctors possible finding that I should be able to work. WTH? I've paid over $20,000 in premiums over the years and I'm getting this type of treatment. You never know how things are going to turn out until you really need it. When I established this policy it was obviously to keep me from losing everything I own should I not be able to work. Never would I imagine that I would have to jump through so many hoops. I still have to pay premiums while they review the claim. Did I say…that I've been off since October 2013. DO YOUR RESEARCH!

For me I refused the charge, cancelled my card and I'm going to take this as far as I can.

The funeral home and I have provided the Order Confirming Administratix from the county courthouse, the death certificate of the deceased (my step-father), death certificate of his named beneficiary (my mother), the taxpayer ID number for his estate, and you are denying payment to the funeral home because you can't conclude from the information provided to you that I am the Administratix/executrix/personal representative of the estate or that his estate has been set up. However, the following companies have been nothing but accommodating in providing their services after receiving the same information: #erie_insurance #ATT #toyota #wellsfargo #bbtbank

I'm already dealing with my step-father's death, dreading the sell of my childhood home, paying his mortgage and two car payments, raising my daughter who will never remember two amazing grandparents, and handling his estate from out-of-state.  Thank you for adding this additional inconvenience.

Whether you like history or not, you cannot deny that one’s previous actions give insight into their future actions. New York Life Insurance Company has a rich history of being a great place for women to work, and the future of that streak seems bright. The history dates back to the 1800’s as they were the first company in America to hire women life insurance agents, and in the 1980’s they named the first female general counsel of any major insurance company. Since 2001, 11 times NY Life has been recognized by Working Mother Magazine as one of the 100 Best Companies for working mothers. Their dedication to women continues as they partner with #ALPFA to host this year’s Women of ALPFA Summit. Come and meet speakers from New York Life, as well as recruiters. 

Sign up at http://bit.ly/2014NYWoA

WARNING!!! My mother bought life insurance with this company NEW YORK LIFE. She has been struggling to pay her insurance payment every month and still has paid it loyally for ten years. Just the other day at the ten year mark, she got a notice that her payments which were originally $52.00 per month just shot up to $288.00 per month because (they told her) after ten years her premium automatically increases. She was originally told her $52.00 payment was locked in 10 years ago by her sales rep. Absolutely disgusting!!! I always wondered what the catch was. 

From what I understand now is that she now has a choice to either pay $288. a month or change her plan to have higher payments for less insurance, or drop this new ridiculous payment and have no insurance. I am trying to understand why anyone would ever buy life insurance if it goes up to unaffordible amounts when you are less likely to be able to afford it and need it most. Isnt this equivelent to dumping your money down the toilet. Totally misrepresented...I was thinking the gamble was committing to the monthly payment and sticking to it for the rest of your life. 

How terrible it is when you make sacrifices for your family for so long thinking about their well being and you find out it was all for NOTHING!!!

READ THE FINE PRINT OR HAVE AN ATTORNEY INTERPRET ANY COMMITMENTS SUCH AS THIS...CROOKS!

I have had a disability policy with this company for over 25 years. I have been on disability since October of 2013 and have yet to receive a payment. I have been getting the run around from their administrator UNUM. Google UNUM and you will see that they are crooks. Agent.... What's that? I've left numerous messages with my Agent Jim Rutledge and have yet to receive the courtesy of a return call. I have to continue paying premiums until they deem me disabled. Wth? I calculate that I have paid out over $20,000 in premiums over the past 25 years. If I can't work due to a disability, and I pay premiums for instances like this, why am I still waiting to get paid. Never again!!!!!
